<br>
Me: “Hello”<br>
Lady: “Hello, Mr. Adel. This is Laura with Ameritech and we would like to offer you aDSL!”<br>
Me: “Woot, what do I have to do?”<br>
Lady: “Just lemme know if you want the aDSL to come in through this phone or you fax line.”<br>
Me: “Ok, lets use the fax line. Oh, and I have 3 computers, will I be able to hook them all up to the aDSL?”<br>
Lady: “Yep, all you’ll need to do is go buy a Router from Circuit City and some Ethernet cards. The aDSL will be activated on November 12th and we will be sending you the aDSL modem in the mail shortly.”<br>
Me: “Sounds good, thanks bye.”<br>
<br>
And so it began…<br>
<br>
The thing about this service is that you hook everything up yourself. Ameritech sends you a USB aDSL modem that plugs in right through your phone jack. It’s really easy and that’s not where the problem comes in. <br>
<br>
Before the activation date I went out and bought all the needed items to network my three computers. 3 Ethernet cards, Cat5 Cable, and 1 Router. I hooked it all up and it works fine. Installed Microsoft Internet Connection Sharing on the computer that was going to be the “master” and I was all set to go. <br>
<br>
November 12 hits and the modem comes in the mail, woot! I hook it up to the main computer and of course it doesn’t work. <br>
<br>
So I call Ameritech.<br>
<br>
Me: “Hi, I was just calling to make sure that my aDSL line was activated today”<br>
Guy: “Ok, lemme type your info in here and we’ll wait for the status to pop up”<br>
    --we both wait in awkward silence—<br>
Guy: “Ok, seems your line has been delayed and won’t be activated until November 20.”<br>
Me: “Damn, why the delay?”<br>
Guy: “The report doesn’t say”<br>
Me: “Was anyone going to call me and tell me it was delayed?”<br>
Guy: “We tried to call earlier and no one was home”<br>
<br>
@#%$! I was home all day, not using the phone, and at worst they could have left a message on my voice mail. Oh well.<br>
<br>
November 20th rolls around…hey whadda know the aDSL isn’t working. <br>
<br>
Lets call Ameritech.<br>
<br>
Me: “Hi, I’m checking on the status of my aDSL, it was supposed to be activated today.”<br>
Lady: “It takes 24 hours to update our computers, call back tomorrow sir.”<br>
 <br>
November 21st(I know this is kinda long, but this is where things get good!)<br>
<br>
Call Ameritech…<br>
<br>
Me: “Hi, I’m calling to check the status of my aDSL line.”<br>
Guy:  “It’s not up and running”<br>
Me: “Yeah, I know”<br>
Guy: “Lets see if the engineer typed a reason why.”<br>
        --pause—<br>
Guy: “Ah yes, your aDSL line is not running and it is on hold”<br>
Me: “When will it be activated?”<br>
Guy: “Someday”<br>
Me: “Someday?”<br>
Guy: “Yes, we are not sure when.”<br>
Me: “Ok, um…how will I know when it is working?”<br>
Guy: “Just keep the USB modem plugged in and when the light turns green it’s working.”<br>
Me: “Ok, bye” grrrrrrrr<br>
<br>
I am a bit angry at this point for a few reasons. <br>
  1) Ameritech called me and told me they could give me aDSL. I didn’t go to them and seek this out. <br>
  2) I’ve got a network hooked up and collecting dust and it was not inexpensive to set up. From the Router to the cables to the Ethernet cards. I wouldn’t have made these purchases if I wasn’t going to be getting aDSL. <br>
  3) The phone call and realizations I made today(see below)<br>
<br>
Call Ameritech…<br>
<br>
Me: “Hi, I was supposed to get aDSL activated on November 12th and now it’s the 27th and it’s not working and I was wondering if you guys had a estimated date?”<br>
Lady: “Ah yes, it seems your work service request has been canceled.”<br>
Me: “What?”<br>
Lady: “Your order has been canceled because it was going to take more then 30 days.”<br>
Me: “Why was it going to take 30 days? You called me and talked me into buying this service in the first place!”<br>
Lady: “It seems we do not have the required resources at this time. My screen tells me that we have an estimated date to be ready on December 31st.”<br>
Me: “Ok, so will my aDSL be active on December 31?”<br>
Lady: “No, since it was going to take more then 30 days you will have to re-order the service with us.”<br>
Me: “Ok, hey am I going to be charged the $200 for the modem you guys sent me?”<br>
Lady: “Lemme transfer you to sales”<br>
<br>
Lady2: “Hi, sir. You will need to repackage the USB modem and all it’s parts. Tape it up and take it to your local UPS station and have them send it back to us. There is a return address on the box.”<br>
Me: “But I am going to order the service once December 31st hits, it should be ready by then.”<br>
Lady2: “I know sir, but when you re-order the service you have to buy the modem again.”<br>
Me: “But I already have the modem”<br>
Lady2: “Yes, but you need to return it so we don’t charge you for it. Because when you order the service again on December 31 you will have to buy the modem. You don’t want to buy two modems do you?”<br>
Me: “No…look this is stupid and it’s a hassle. We know that I want your Ameritech aDSL service. I have the equipment and I am just waiting for you guys to activate the phone line. Wouldn’t it make sense for me to keep the modem and wait for the line to be ready?<br>
Lady2: “I’m sorry sir, but there’s nothing I can do”<br>
--click—<br>
<br>
Ok so I have to return this stupid USB modem I have or I get charged $200 dollars for it and then I would have to buy another one on December 31st when I re-ordered my service. Barring all the confusion that went on I don’t think Ameritech ever planned on telling me this! No one informed me that my service was CANCELED and my Modem should be returned! No one told me I’d have to buy another modem if I wanted to order the service again! Jesus they called me, I didn’t ask for this frustration. If someone calls you up and offers you a service and you agree to buy it don’t you think they would be able to fulfill their end of the bargain?!? Ok, sorry this got way too long, lol. I just had to get this outta my system.<br>
<br>
F U Ameritech.<br>
<br>
...it's not all for nought I guess. I used my useless network to print stuff off my other computer one day because this one ran out of ink.<br>
