<br>
Don't tell them you have multiple computers, though.  Instead, you need to use a hub/router designed for cable connections.  The hub will spoof the cable modem into thinking it's the PC, and all the PCs hide behind it.  It's fancy-ass computer stuff, but you don't need to do anything except:<br>
<br>
1. Let AT&amp;T get everything running for you with one of your computers.<br>
<br>
